### lookupTarget {#a9a9a7989eeb174879ae8581e33e61824}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>const Target &#42; TargetRegistry::lookupTarget (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> ArchName, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/triple">Triple</a> &amp; TheTriple, std::string &amp; Error)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
lookupTarget - Lookup a target based on an architecture name and a target triple.

If the architecture name is non-empty, then the lookup is done by architecture. Otherwise, the target triple is used.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="ArchName">- The architecture to use for finding a target.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="TheTriple">- The triple to use for finding a target. The triple is updated with canonical architecture name if a lookup by architecture is done.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="<a href=&quot;/docs/api/classes/llvm/error&quot;>Error</a>">- On failure, an error string describing why no target was found.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<MemberDefinition
